{"id": "work_c816709e-d287-5267-8ee1-a1302f909064", "title": "Generating single microwave photons in a circuit", "sources": [{"source": "dtic", "id": "pub.1029213004"}], "last_updated": "2026-03-09T19:36:38.397745", "abstract": "On-chip quantum opticsMicrowaves are already exploited in conventional communication technologies, from long-distance broadcasts to short-distance signals within a computer chip. But they may also be used in a quantum computer for communication between distant quantum bits (qubits). An efficient on-chip, on-demand source of single microwave photons has now been developed, with characteristics that may make it suitable for processing quantum information in a circuit of superconducting qubits. This is the first report of a superconducting qubit mapped onto a &#x27;flying qubit&#x27;, a mobile bit of quantum information that is one of the &#x27;DiVincenzo criteria&#x27; for quantum computing.", "publication_date": "2007-09-01", "doi": "10.1038/nature06126", "url": "https://dtic.dimensions.ai/details/publication/pub.1029213004?and_facet_researcher=ur.015527265674.84", "citation_count": 0, "authors": [{"author_id": "author_14dc1e6b-eb21-5940-96fc-7d8b84783e30", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_78542dd0-c538-5434-8d2c-fe6f77c8cde3", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_346a830e-67fe-5ca2-9afe-fc59ec3e813d", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_1b8386ba-6df7-57eb-9e5d-a636a0c3dd54", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_161bc9f4-7392-5c2b-9b2f-a41ce9b126d2", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_a9877bfb-d7df-5d77-8b9d-194867128b30", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_d2b8b900-5488-5f87-ab9d-06fb3b0ff50b", "org_id": "org_cf6683eb-25ad-50fe-a19d-855f6e3e86df"}, {"author_id": "author_afd64421-6c30-5068-bae3-76e